## PowerShell Module: IIS-Handler

All IIS operations (`IIS-DeployApp.ps1`, `IIS-UninstallApp.ps1`, `IIS-RedeployAll.ps1`, `Test-IISSite.ps1`) are powered by the **IIS-Handler** PowerShell module:

| Item | Detail |
|------|--------|
| **Module** | `IIS-Handler` |
| **Source** | `C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\_Modules\IIS-Handler\IIS-Handler.psm1` |
| **On PSModulePath** | Yes -- loaded via `Import-Module IIS-Handler -Force` |
| **Key functions** | `Deploy-IISSite`, `Uninstall-IISSite`, `Test-IISSite`, `Install-OurWinApp` |

`Deploy-IISSite` implements the 10-step deploy process: Teardown → Install files → Create app pool → Create virtual app → Generate web.config → Set permissions → Firewall rules → Start → Verify → Health check.

`Install-OurWinApp` copies published files from the staging share (`\\server\DedgeCommon\Software\DedgeWinApps\<AppName>`) to the local install path (`$env:OptPath\DedgeWinApps\<AppName>`).

## IIS-DeployApp Scripts

| Script | Path | Purpose |
|--------|------|---------|
| `IIS-DeployApp.ps1` | `C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\WebSites\IIS-DeployApp\` | Deploy/update one app from template |
| `IIS-UninstallApp.ps1` | Same folder | Remove one virtual app + app pool + firewall |
| `IIS-RedeployAll.ps1` | Same folder | Teardown all + iisreset + redeploy all from templates |
| `Test-IISSite.ps1` | Same folder | Diagnostics and health checks |
| `_deploy.ps1` | Same folder | Sync scripts and templates to servers |

After editing any IIS-DeployApp scripts or templates, run `_deploy.ps1` to push changes to servers.

## Full Deploy Sequence (publish + IIS + verify)

```powershell
# 1. Build and publish all apps to staging
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgeAuth\Build-And-Publish-ALL.ps1"

# 2. Deploy from staging to local IIS (teardown + rebuild all)
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\WebSites\IIS-DeployApp\IIS-RedeployAll.ps1"

# 3. Verify with screenshots, email, and SMS
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\GrabScreenShot\Invoke-GrabScreenShot.ps1"
```

